Political Capital: Hungarian Guard increases State risk
According to the Political Capital Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysis Division), the activities of the Hungarian Guard, founded this August with the support of the "movement for a better Hungary", have raised the risk of Hungary and the region in several respects.
Among other things, the Institute's "risk warning report" states: in connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk is the "enhancement of the already existing ethnic tensions between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy population in Hungary, which could even lead to violent ethnic confrontations in the short term".
The main reason for this is the Hungarian Guard strategy, which is probably aimed at provocation of such a conflict, according to the Research Institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure on the part of the political leaders: "People of public life have left the discussion of the Roma question to representatives of radical political groups, who have now built up their political strategy on the Roma-Hungary gender".
It is believed that this would exacerbate the problem, make reasonable dialogue impossible, promote extremities, and increase the likelihood of violent conflicts.
The research institute also believes that the activities of the Hungarian Guard have been significantly damaged, not least thanks to the enormous attention given by the local and foreign media, "the image of Hungary abroad, especially in terms of confidence in stability and democratic maturity".
We remember that since autumn 2006 the reorganisation of radical and extreme right groups in Hungary has been constantly under way, so that since summer 2007 several organisations called "national self-defence society" have been established.
"These groups are meant to define themselves as civil organizations, while openly boasting of preparing their members - sometimes armed - for defence tasks (disaster protection, state defence, order-keeping), calling for the inability of the police, army, or state itself," it said.
And further: all this happens in accordance with that method, which tries to seduce various political aspirations, based on the political and party perversion of the population, as a bourgeois initiative.
The emphasis on the civil character and the form of the association is not merely on the circumvention of legal hurdles that may arise in the course of the registration at court - it is at the same time a political strategy.
As the analysis can be seen, the activities of the Hungarian Guard represent a risk-raising factor for relations with neighbouring countries as well.
"In recent months, Hungarian Guards have been cited as a potential source of danger in several neighbouring countries, as some ultra-nationalist politicians from certain neighbouring countries see the confirmation of their own anti-Hungary policy in the creation of the Hungarian Guard.
All of this has an impact on the political stability of the region" - said it.
From the point of view of the Research Institute, the establishment of the Hungarian Guard is not a single phenomenon in Central Eastern Europe, so the political risk for the whole region has increased.
As reported, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are comparable to those of the Bulgarian National Guard, whose founding was announced in August 2007 by the Bulgarian National Union (BNU).
