Which insurance is best for me?
The car insurance covering a possible damage caused by the driver includes a high cost, which in turn depends on different factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driver's licence, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
To own a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the appropriate car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you have to be clear about what we're dealing with here.
Auto insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the insurance premium agreed and is obliged, in return for damages, to present the amount of the compensation in question.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance which is composed of several factors, including age, gender, the time of issue of the driving licence, family status, the type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance undertakings shall determine their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contributions are also due in the event of a higher risk of accident.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to make fewer contributions because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate due to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and thus also according to the company's conviction, they tend to be less accidents than single persons.
The benefits attached to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and therefore also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
Insurance must take a number of points into account when setting up the premium.
For this reason, the driver also needs to study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
We are now listing the most important points that should be considered when choosing insurance in order not only to make a performance-oriented choice but also to make a price-oriented choice.
The 25-year-olds meet numerous obstacles in choosing cheap insurance, such as low driving practices and young driving licences.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance policy to take out full insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full case with self-share, so that the benefits of full insurance cover but are offered at a low price.
This type of contract includes that the customer must pay part of the amount resulting from the damage itself.
The amount is determined prior to the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium. This is higher than the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, the main representative of Spain at First Europe, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is the extended insurance policy, which assures customers against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused by their own car.
Moreover, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years old, it is in your hands to reduce insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit card is a reduction in the basic rate of the insurance company concerned.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase in tariffs.
The amount of credits and fines depends on the company and its revenues.
If the company has a successful year behind it, it may allow to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. Reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it is most appropriate to opt for full insurance with self-employment.
Usually young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, the Spanish President of the European company explains, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been removed.
Nevertheless, in the case of a married customer who has no children, it is more advisable to take out full insurance; of course, only if it allows the financial situation of the corresponding person.
On the part of the insurers, couples with children are considered to be customers with the lowest accident rate, and consequently their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, full insurance with self-employment (in the case of an amount of EUR 300) would be the best option. If you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy should be used only for the third vehicle year.
They are generally more relaxed and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera states.
For pensioners, it is possible to take out full insurance with self-employment (with an amount of EUR 150) or an extended insurance, which will only be used with a sufficiently high credit card.
Finally, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough choice that corresponds to our personal situation.
